<div id="outline-container-org01b7b48" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org01b7b48">Simple Text Oriented Messeging protocol&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;<span class="tag"><span class="stomp">stomp</span></span></h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org01b7b48">
<p>
STOMP is a simple text based protocol for working with <a href="../20221219225036-message_oriented_middleware.html#ID-8a9b8114-4064-48ed-8057-5f6a7c512ea1">Message oriented middleware</a>.
It is very simular to the Well Known <a href="20221219225206-http.html#ID-55fa6669-d1f4-4956-abf0-a0c3c2aac23b">HTTP</a>, it works over <a href="20221219225308-tcp.html#ID-a75d2660-481e-4c42-98bf-358b08f8c030">TCP</a>.
Stomp is an alterntive to other messaging protocoles that cover a small subset of messaging operations rather then providing a comprehisive messaging api.
</p>
</div>


<div id="outline-container-org72d6b9d" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org72d6b9d">Overview</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org72d6b9d">
<p>
It is a frame based protocol. Frames are moddeled on <a href="20221219225206-http.html#ID-55fa6669-d1f4-4956-abf0-a0c3c2aac23b">HTTP</a>.
A frame is a command, a set of optional headers and an optional body. By defualt it is textbased but also can transmit binary messages.
</p>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org728ab8a" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org728ab8a">Commands</h3>
